Description:
Agfa box (Annotation: "An das Bazierksbauamt Schloss linker Flügel")

- Reproductions of engravings for the calendar (see Kiste 2, Lose Akte 25).
- Essay (reprint): 'Rubens's Munich Lion Hunt: Its Sources and Significance' by David Rosand in "The Art Bulletin", 1969 (Annotation on the cover: "Rubens Löwenjagd")
- Correspondence (inside "The Art Bulletin") with David Rosand dated 1969
- Reproductions of different artworks ('The Rape of the Daughters of Leucippus', 'The Baptism of Christ', etc.)
- Notes about The Baptism of Christ dated 1968
- Cover of "The Illustrated London News" (Christmas number, 1929)
- Article about Rubens by Ernst Felix Weiss
- Unbound pages about Rubens
